: <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.StringComparison?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph>.","pos":[34809,34889],"source":"Default interpretation: <xref:System.StringComparison?displayProperty=fullName>."},{"content":"When you store any data in a collection, or read persisted data from a file or database into a collection, switching the current culture can invalidate the invariants in the collection.","pos":[34896,35081]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Array.BinarySearch%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> method assumes that the elements in the array to be searched are already sorted.","pos":[35082,35227],"source":" The <xref:System.Array.BinarySearch%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method assumes that the elements in the array to be searched are already sorted."},{"content":"To sort any string element in the array, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Array.Sort%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> method calls the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.String.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> method to order individual elements.","pos":[35228,35436],"source":" To sort any string element in the array, the <xref:System.Array.Sort%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method calls the <xref:System.String.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method to order individual elements."},{"content":"Using a culture-sensitive comparer can be dangerous if the culture changes between the time that the array is sorted and its contents are searched.","pos":[35437,35584]},{"content":"For example, in the following code, storage and retrieval operate on the comparer that is provided implicitly by the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture`</ph> property.","pos":[35585,35749],"source":" For example, in the following code, storage and retrieval operate on the comparer that is provided implicitly by the `Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture` property."},{"content":"If the culture can change between the calls to <ph id=\"ph1\">`StoreNames`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`DoesNameExist`</ph>, and especially if the array contents are persisted somewhere between the two method calls, the binary search may fail.","pos":[35750,35949],"source":" If the culture can change between the calls to `StoreNames` and `DoesNameExist`, and especially if the array contents are persisted somewhere between the two method calls, the binary search may fail."},{"content":"A recommended variation appears in the following example, which uses the same ordinal (culture-insensitive) comparison method both to sort and to search the array.","pos":[36268,36431]},{"content":"The change code is reflected in the lines labeled <ph id=\"ph1\">`Line A`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`Line B`</ph> in the two examples.","pos":[36432,36524],"source":" The change code is reflected in the lines labeled `Line A` and `Line B` in the two examples."},{"content":"If this data is persisted and moved across cultures, and sorting is used to present this data to the user, you might consider using <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.StringComparison?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph>, which operates linguistically for better user output but is unaffected by changes in culture.","pos":[36843,37125],"source":"If this data is persisted and moved across cultures, and sorting is used to present this data to the user, you might consider using <xref:System.StringComparison?displayProperty=fullName>, which operates linguistically for better user output but is unaffected by changes in culture."},{"content":"The following example modifies the two previous examples to use the invariant culture for sorting and searching the array.","pos":[37126,37248]},{"pos":[37570,37612],"content":"Collections Example: Hashtable Constructor","linkify":"Collections Example: Hashtable Constructor","nodes":[{"content":"Collections Example: Hashtable Constructor","pos":[0,42]}]},{"content":"Hashing strings provides a second example of an operation that is affected by the way in which strings are compared.","pos":[37616,37732]},{"content"